    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-09-07T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-09-07T00:00:00-05:00" n="973"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d973">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72111/156</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The British Ambassador</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_SRSCA1"
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Spring Rice</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <p rend="center">
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">memorandum</hi>
                </p>
                <p>The British Ambassador presents his compliments to the Secretary of State of the
                    United States and, with reference to his note No. 302 of September 4, has the
                    honour to state that he is informed by the British Consul General that the
                    steamship <hi rend="italic">Adriatic</hi>, which sailed from New York on
                    September 3 with four guns mounted and 200 rounds of ammunition, took 28
                    first-class passengers, 43 second, and 89 third. She also took 637 bags of mail
                    and a general cargo of provisions and manufactured goods. She had no war
                    material on board and no army reservists.</p>
                <p>These data bear out the assurances that the <hi rend="italic">Adriatic</hi> is
                    bound on a peaceful commercial voyage and that her armament is destined solely
                    for defensive purposes.</p>
                <closer>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">British Embassy</hi>, <lb/>
                    <dateline rendition="#left">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-09-07">
                            <hi rend="italic">September 7, 1914</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>. <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received September 10</hi>.] </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
